onance in other disciplines, which is illustrated by the writings of the American existential psychotherapist Rollo May. This volume outlines the reciprocal influences of both thinkers by looking at the topics of fear, freedom, love, the demonic, power, and myth, and their significance for a contemporary examination of these topics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAngst. 4aFreiheit. 4aMacht. 4aMay, Rollo. 4aMythos. 4aTillich, Paul.  aMay, Rollo.  aTillich, Paul.  afear.  afreedom.  amyth.  apower.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107806730 cprintz978311078032140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311078058140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110780581423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110780581/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023